<article>
    <h1>Hua Ting&#x2019;s Moon&#xAD;cake Col&#xAD;lec&#xAD;tion</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200904/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-09-04"><time>2020-09-04</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE | HAPPENINGS</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>The award-win­ning Chi­nese restau­rant has un­veiled its moon­cake range fea­tur­ing both tra­di­tional favourites and cre­ative flavours made with or­ganic in­gre­di­ents.</p>
    <p>This year’s high­light is the sour plum with roasted or­ganic hazel­nut snowskin moon­cake ($70 for a box of eight). Spe­cially im­ported from Hong Kong, the sour plums are steamed and ground for hours to smoothen the fill­ing. Or­ganic Turk­ish hazel­nuts are baked till fra­grant and mixed with the fill­ing.</p>
    <p>Those who en­joy a dash of al­co­hol in their moon­cakes can go for the white lo­tus paste with cham­pagne ganache or the blue­berry with vin­tage hua diao wine.</p>
    <p>WHERE: Or­chard Ho­tel Sin­ga­pore,</p>
    <p>442 Or­chard Road</p>
    <p>MRT: Or­chard</p>
    <p>WHEN: Till Oct 1</p>
    <p>INFO: bit.ly/3bnEWxU</p>


